MetaDataVersion.Name: Study CDISC01, Data Definitions
MetaDataVersion.def:ComputationMethod: QTcB = QT interval / square root of (60 / heart rate)
QTcF = QT interval / cubic root of (60 / heart rate)

ItemDef.Name: AETRTEM
ItemDef.Comment: If it was not present prior to the RFSTDTC, or it was present prior to the RFSTDTC but increased in severity during the treatment period then equal Y..
ItemDef.def:Label: Treatment Emergent Flag

ItemDef.Name: LBCLSIG
ItemDef.Comment: Only created if value qualifies as potentially clinically significant high or low based on the high and low ranges specified in the Statitical Analysis Plan..
ItemDef.def:Label: Clinically Significant

ItemDef.Name: RAND
ItemDef.Comment: Randomization Population flag will be set to Y for subjects who were randomized
ItemDef.def:Label: Randomized Population Flag

ItemDef.Name: SAFETY
ItemDef.Comment: Safety Population flag will be set to Y for randomized subjects who took at least one dose study medication
ItemDef.def:Label: Safety Population Flag

ItemDef.Name: VSCLSIG
ItemDef.Comment: Only created if value qualifies as potentially clinically significant high or low based on the high and low ranges specified in the Statitical Analysis Plan..
ItemDef.def:Label: Clinically Significant

ItemDef.Name: USUBJID
ItemDef.Comment: Concatenation of STUDYID.SUBJID
ItemDef.def:Label: Unique Subject Identifier

ItemDef.Name: AESEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: AETERM
ItemDef.def:Label: Reported Term for the Adverse Event

ItemDef.Name: AESTDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = AESTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if AESTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. AESTDTC - RFSTDTC if AESTDTC precedes RFSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Start of Adverse Event

ItemDef.Name: AEENDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = AEENDTC -RFSTDTC+1 if AEENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC. AEENDTC - RFSTDTC if AEENDTC precedes RFSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of End of Adverse Event

ItemDef.Name: CMSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: CMTRT
ItemDef.def:Label: Reported Name of Drug, Med, or Therapy

ItemDef.Name: CMCLAS
ItemDef.Comment: Coded to ATC level 3 Term based on CMINDC
ItemDef.def:Label: Medication Class

ItemDef.Name: CMCLASCD
ItemDef.Comment: Coded to ATC level 3 Code based on CMINDC
ItemDef.def:Label: Medication Class Code

ItemDef.Name: CMSTDY
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: CMSTDTC - RFSTDTC +1 if CMSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, CMSTDTC - RFSTDTC if CMSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Start of Medication

ItemDef.Name: CMENDY
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: CMENDTC - RFSTDTC +1 if CMENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, CMENDTC - RFSTDTC if CMENDTC precedes RFSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of End of Medication

ItemDef.Name: DASEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: DASTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to DAORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Assessment Result in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: DASTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to numeric value of DAORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units

ItemDef.Name: VISITNUM
ItemDef.Comment: Derived based on DADTC using the SV domain
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit Number

ItemDef.Name: VISIT
ItemDef.Comment: Assigned from the TV domain based on the VISITNUM
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit Name

ItemDef.Name: DADY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = DADTC - RFSTDTC+1 if DADTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = DADTC - RFSTDTC if DADTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Accountability Assessment

ItemDef.Name: RFSTDTC
ItemDef.Comment: For safety subjects equal to first date/time of study drug. Null for screen failures.
ItemDef.def:Label: Subject Reference Start Date/Time

ItemDef.Name: RFENDTC
ItemDef.Comment: For safety subjects = termination date. Null for screen failures.
ItemDef.def:Label: Subject Reference End Date/Time

ItemDef.Name: AGE
ItemDef.Comment: Screening Date - Birth date

ItemDef.Name: AGEU
ItemDef.Comment: Defaulted to YEARS
ItemDef.def:Label: Age Units

ItemDef.Name: ARMCD
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from arm code in TRIAL ARM (TA) based on Randomization Number.
ItemDef.def:Label: Planned Arm Code

ItemDef.Name: ARM
ItemDef.Comment: From description of arm in TRIAL ARM (TA) based on Randomization Number
ItemDef.def:Label: Description of Planned Arm

ItemDef.Name: DSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: DSTERM
ItemDef.def:Label: Reported Term for the Disposition Event

ItemDef.Name: DSDECOD
ItemDef.Comment: CRF controlled terminology was mapped to match CDISC controlled terminology.
ItemDef.def:Label: Standardized Disposition Term

ItemDef.Name: DSSTDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = DSSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if DSSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; Calculation = DSSTDTC - RFSTDTC if DSSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC; Equal to missing if RFSTDTC is missing.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Start of Disposition Event

ItemDef.Name: EGSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: EGSPID
ItemDef.Comment: ECG parameter ordering variable
ItemDef.def:Label: Sponsor-Defined Identifier

ItemDef.Name: EGTESTCD
ItemDef.def:Label: ECG Test or Examination Short Name

ItemDef.Name: EGPOS
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to SUPINE
ItemDef.def:Label: ECG Position of Subject

ItemDef.Name: EGORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Result or Finding in Original Units

ItemDef.Name: EGSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Data collected in non-standard units is converted using standard conversion factors to standard units.
ItemDef.def:Label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: EGSTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: When EGSTRESC contains numeric data the numeric equivalent is derived in EGSTRESN
ItemDef.def:Label: Numeric Result/Finding in Standard Units

ItemDef.Name: EGBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Derivation of baseline: Safety subjects only: EGBLFL=Y for last non missing record on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
ItemDef.def:Label: Baseline Flag

ItemDef.Name: EGDRVFL
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to Y for derived EGTESTCDs QTCB and QTCF
ItemDef.def:Label: Derived Flag

ItemDef.Name: EGEVAL
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to INVESTIGATOR for CRF data

ItemDef.Name: EGDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = EGDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EGDTC is on or after RFTSDTC, Calculation = EGDTC - RFSTDTC if EGDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of ECG

ItemDef.Name: EXSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: EXTRT
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from ARM, ARMCD
ItemDef.def:Label: Name of Actual Treatment

ItemDef.Name: EXDOSE
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from ARM, ARMCD
ItemDef.def:Label: Dose per Administration

ItemDef.Name: EXDOSU
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from ARM, ARMCD - equal to mg
ItemDef.def:Label: Dose Units

ItemDef.Name: EXDOSTOT
ItemDef.Comment: Derived: Number of administrations per day (QVAL where QNAM=SMNO) times EXDOSE
ItemDef.def:Label: Total Daily Dose

ItemDef.Name: EXSTDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC+1 if EXSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = EXSTDTC - RFSTDTC if EXSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Start of Treatment

ItemDef.Name: EXENDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = EXENDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if EXENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = EXENDTC - RFSTDTC if EXENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of End of Treatment

ItemDef.Name: IESEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: IESTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from IEORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: I/E Criterion Result in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: LBSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: LBREFID
ItemDef.Comment: Accession number
ItemDef.def:Label: Specimen ID

ItemDef.Name: LBTESTCD
ItemDef.def:Label: Lab Test or Examination Short Name

ItemDef.Name: LBORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Result or Finding in Original Units

ItemDef.Name: LBORNRLO
ItemDef.def:Label: Reference Range Lower Limit in Orig Unit

ItemDef.Name: LBORNRHI
ItemDef.def:Label: Reference Range Upper Limit in Orig Unit

ItemDef.Name: LBSTNRC
ItemDef.def:Label: Reference Range for Char Rslt-Std Units

ItemDef.Name: LBNRIND
ItemDef.Comment: Reference Range Indicator based upon standard results and ranges.
ItemDef.def:Label: Reference Range Indicator

ItemDef.Name: LBBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Derivation of baseline: Safety subjects only: LBBLFL=Y for last non missing record on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
ItemDef.def:Label: Baseline Flag

ItemDef.Name: VISITNUM
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from Visit, Day Number and Trial Visit (TV).
ItemDef.def:Label: Visit Number

ItemDef.Name: LBDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = LBDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if LBDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = LBDTC - RFSTDTC if LBDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Specimen Collection

ItemDef.Name: MHSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: MHTERM
ItemDef.def:Label: Reported Term for the Medical History

ItemDef.Name: MHBODSYS
ItemDef.Comment: Assigned for Medical History but not Psychiatric History
ItemDef.def:Label: Body System or Organ Class

ItemDef.Name: MHSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: Start Date/Time of Medical History Event

ItemDef.Name: PESEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: PESTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Derived from PEORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: PEDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = PEDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if PEDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = PEDTC - RFSTDTC if PEDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Examination

ItemDef.Name: QSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: QSSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: If questionnaire result is a numerically relevant code then code stored here; else character result equal to QSORRES. Character results contain mixed case data.
ItemDef.def:Label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: QSSTRESN
ItemDef.Comment: When QSORRES is numeric then QSSTRESN equal to numeric result
ItemDef.def:Label: Numeric Finding in Standard Units

ItemDef.Name: QSBLFL
ItemDef.Comment: Derivation of baseline: Safety subjects only: QSBLFL=Y for last non missing record on or before the first dose date (RFSTDTC).
ItemDef.def:Label: Baseline Flag

ItemDef.Name: QSDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = QSDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if QSDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = QSDTC - RFSTDTC if QSDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Finding

ItemDef.Name: SCSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: SCORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Result or Finding in Original Units

ItemDef.Name: SCSTRESC
ItemDef.Comment: Equal to SCORRES
ItemDef.def:Label: Character Result/Finding in Std Format

ItemDef.Name: SCDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = SCDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if SCDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = SCDTC - RFSTDTC if SCDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Examination

ItemDef.Name: SESEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: SESTDTC
ItemDef.Comment: If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVSTDTC where VISIT = SCREENING or from DS where DSDECOD = 'INFORMED CONSENT', whichever is earliest. If Element = EOS, derived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT. For treatment Elements, derived from first EXSTDTC for the element.
ItemDef.def:Label: Start Date/Time of Element

ItemDef.Name: SEENDTC
ItemDef.Comment: If Element = SCREEN, derived from SVENDTC where VISIT = SCREENING. If Element = EOS, derived from DS where DSCAT = DISPOSITION EVENT or from the latest EXENDTC from EX whichever is later. For treatment Elements, derived from last EXENDTC for the element .
ItemDef.def:Label: End Date/Time of Element

ItemDef.Name: TAETORD
ItemDef.def:Label: Planned Order of Elements within Arm

ItemDef.Name: SVENDTC
ItemDef.Comment: Defaulted to SVSTDTC
ItemDef.def:Label: End Date/Time of Visit

ItemDef.Name: SVSTDY
ItemDef.Comment: Calculation: = SVSTDTC-RFSTDTC+1 if SVSTDTC is on or after RFSTDTC, Calculation = SVSTDTC - RFSTDTC if SVSTDTC precedes RFSTDTC.
ItemDef.def:Label: Study Day of Start of Visit

ItemDef.Name: TSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each TSPARM in the domain.
ItemDef.def:Label: Sequence Number

ItemDef.Name: VSSEQ
ItemDef.Comment: Sequential number identifying records within each USUBJID and generated using the key sequence of the domain.

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESC

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESN

ItemDef.Name: VSSTRESU

ItemDef.Name: VSBLFL

ItemDef.Name: EXCL01
ItemDef.def:Label: Is pregnant, nursing, or planning to become pregnant within 6 months of last study treatment

ItemDef.Name: EXCL02
ItemDef.def:Label: Is unable or unwilling to undergo multiple venipunctures

ItemDef.Name: EXCL03
ItemDef.def:Label: Is known to have had a substance abuse (drug or alcohol) problem within the previous 3 years

ItemDef.Name: INCL02
ItemDef.def:Label: Has Xyz disease of at least 10 weeks duration confirmed by biopsy

ItemDef.Name: INCL03
ItemDef.def:Label: Did not respond to a standard course of medication Abc

ItemDef.Name: CSDD
